ttp://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Young, full of hate, a formless arm of Innoruuk appears.</span><hr size=1> (Young Darkrayne does in fact spread the words of Hate. Observe the true story below.)<br>
<br>
Two Teir’Dal meet in the dark forest of Nektulos. They stand near the fallen tree where the young hunt. One is loyal to Innoruuk and the other has forsaken hate in favor of Mithaniel Marr.<br>
<br>
Darkrayne says, 'And who might you be?'<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'You are a member of the Guild Violent Harvest?'<br>
Selveterm frowns at Darkrayne.<br>
Darkrayne says, 'I am new to them but i am a part'<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'You hold Innoruuk dear to your heart? Are you a slave? Do you enjoy having your life belong to another?'<br>
<br>
Darkrayne says, 'I am NOT a slave i choose to serve him'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'The Father is my life blood and yours! i will not Tolerate such Heresy!'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Prepare to die'<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'You CHOOSE! what choice! death or slavery!'<br>
<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Then you are weak'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Hate is what makes The Chosen the strongest'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Of ALL races in Norrath'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'I am willing to give my life for the better of His will'<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'Am I? who is weak, the one who in rage slays all around him destroying all that has the potential to benefit? Or i who extend my heart and my love and forge bonds stronger than steel between others and myself'<br>
<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Love is for the foolish'<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'Your life? what IS your life? are you a meaningless implement of death and destruction? what purpose do you serve '<br>
<br>
Darkrayne says, 'I Serve The Father, my purpose is His'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Meaningless in no such way'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Even the slightest that i can bring'<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'Innoruuk hates all, especially that which he cannot control. Love, mercy, freedom all these are beyond his conception and his power'<br>
<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Those are the powers of the inferiors'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'He wants no part in such'<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'Have you ever asked what his purpose is? I would know! I have raised my sword in dark TRiumph to his fury i have tasted the blood of my fallen foes and it is meaningless slaughter that no matter how hard you try to disguise it, it is just that'<br>
<br>
Darkrayne says, 'A utopia'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'One that neither yourself or myself could begin to understand'<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'Utopia, what does he believe in? death blood and rage? your Utopia would be a blasted waitstland filled with bloated corpses sulferous fumes and entropy'<br>
<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Draw your sword show me how much you truly hate this .'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'I will show you the true power of Hate of Innoruuk!'<br>
<br>
The Northman and Prophet, Benedain enters the forest from the spirit world.<br>
<br>
Benedain laughs aloud from the spirit world.<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'No, i will not give Innoruuk the victory of having my Hate'<br>
<br>
Benedain allows his spirit to take form.<br>
Benedain appears.<br>
<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Come on .'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Do you really believe that following the Lighties is going to make a difference?'<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'I pity you, for you will not die well. You will die before your time with a dagger in your back'<br>
<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Than, will the world will be a better place?'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'They hate you do they not?'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Why do you wish to help them?'<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'I pity you for your blindness'<br>
<br>
Benedain says, 'We do not hate the Tier'dal'<br>
<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Then why do your town guards attack us just in passing?'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Even the lighties have the powers of hate .'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Though it is misguided'<br>
<br>
A Paladin of Erollisi enters the scene, drawn by the commotion and the familiar laugh of his friend Benedain.<br>
<br>
Rohwin says, 'What's going on here?'<br>
<br>
Darkrayne says, 'You would not get away from hate, Innoruuk is in Everyone'<br>
<br>
Benedain says, 'M'lord!'<br>
Benedain kneels before Rohwin in humility and reverence.<br>
<br>
Rohwin snaps to attention and salutes Benedain crisply.<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'Why? We have butchered them for thousands of years! of course they have reason to want us to be gone from their lands!'<br>
Selveterm bows before Rohwin.<br>
Selveterm says, 'Milord Rohwin'<br>
<br>
Rohwin recognizes Selveterm to be the recent advocate of Cursus Honorum and the self-proclaimed long lost son of Sendariu the Redeemed.<br>
<br>
A young Teir’Dal who was hiding in the shadows makes his presence known.<br>
<br>
Houmaruu says, 'Hail, Benedain'<br>
<br>
Darkrayne says, 'You are an embarassment to the Chosen'<br>
Darkrayne says, 'Begone from my sight before i puke on you'<br>
 <br>
Selveterm says, 'I pity you, you just cannot see past yourself can you?'<br>
<br>
Darkrayne says, 'I will enjoy slaying you on the field of battle Lighty'<br>
Darkrayne laughs at Selveterm.<br>
<br>
Houmaruu says, 'May i get buffed?'<br>
<br>
Benedain says, You should declare your obedience to the light, then I shall grant you blessings'<br>
<br>
Houmaruu says, 'I declare'<br>
<br>
Benedain says, 'Yes?  Houmaruu, What do you declare?'<br>
<br>
Houmaruu says, 'My obediance to the light'<br>
<br>
Benedain cheers at Houmaruu.<br>
<br>
Rohwin beams a smile at Houmaruu.<br>
<br>
Benedain bestows the blessings of the spirits upon Houmaruu.<br>
Benedain says, 'Now go, and spread the light!'<br>
<br>
Houmaruu bows before Benedain.<br>
Houmaruu says, 'I will my lord'<br>
Houmaruu runs off into the forest with delight.<br>
<br>
Selveterm looks at Darkrayne sadly.<br>
Selveterm sighs at Rohwin.<br>
<br>
Darkrayne leaves the scene, perhaps because he was feeling outnumbered, or maybe to fetch the city guard, but for what ever reason, he does not return this day.<br>
<br>
Rohwin says, 'I have heard quite enough already, Selveterm, you cannot show the blind where the light is'<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'He just couldnt see could he?'<br>
 <br>
Rohwin says, 'He is blind in every important aspect'<br>
Rohwin says, 'I'm sure he can see us fine, but he cannot see the truth when it lies before him'<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'Yes, though his comments about the townsfolk hating me i think he was correct'<br>
<br>
Rohwin says, 'The path you have chosen for yourself is difficult enough, if you choose to join us then it will only become more difficult'<br>
<br>
Benedain says, 'Indeed, the path of our peoples has been worn down through the ages'<br>
<br>
Rohwin says, 'Your own blood will view you as a traitor'<br>
Rohwin says, 'Many of us who were born in the grace of light will never trust you'<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'Are my kind truly my kind anymore?'<br>
<br>
Rohwin says, 'You will have few friends, life will be difficult'<br>
<br>
Selveterm says, 'I know, but what other choice do i have?'<br>
<br>
Rohwin looks over Selveterm carefully.<br>
Rohwin says, 'You could run . hide in Velious, or on Luclin, few there are even aware of our struggles'<br>
<br>
Selveterm shakes his head.<br>
Selveterm says, 'No i do not run from my problems'<br>
<br>
Benedain says, 'Trust the whispers of your spirits Selveterm, heed their advice, what say them?'<br>
<br>
Rohwin says, 'We shall keep close watch on you . once we hear back from another member of the High Council , then we will let you know what our judgement is'<br>
<br>
Benedain says, 'You have done remarkably well young one, I am sure the Hammers will smile favorably upon you'<br>
<br>
Rohwin says, 'I believe you actions today have been favorable'<br>
<br>
Selveterm bows before Benedain.<br>
Selveterm says, 'Thank you for your words'<br>
<br>
Rohwin and Benedain exit the forest and leave Selveterm to ponder the matters before him.<br>
<br>
<br>
Rohwin Amoure Ardour<br>
